title: It‚Äôs ok, not great
review: I recently tried the elf Hydrating Face Primer, and I have to say, my experience with it has been a bit mixed. While it didn't quite meet my personal expectations, I have noticed that my niece absolutely loves it.One of the standout features of this primer is its lightweight formula. It feels incredibly light on the skin, almost as if you're wearing nothing at all. It doesn't leave any greasy or heavy residue, which is a big plus for those with oily or combination skin.I also appreciate the hydrating properties of this primer. It does a decent job of moisturizing the skin, leaving it feeling soft and supple. I noticed that it helps to smooth out any dry patches, providing a more even canvas for makeup application.Additionally, this primer claims to fill in pores and fine lines, and while it does a decent job in that regard, I didn't notice a significant difference in the appearance of my pores or fine lines. It provided a subtle smoothing effect, but not to the extent that I was hoping for.One aspect that I found particularly beneficial was the natural matte finish. It helped to control shine and kept my makeup looking fresh for a longer duration. However, I did find that it emphasized any texture on my skin, such as acne scars or bumps.While I had mixed feelings about this primer, my niece, who has different skin concerns, absolutely loves it. She has dry skin and found that this primer provided the perfect amount of hydration for her. It also helped to prolong the wear of her makeup and created a smooth base for foundation.In conclusion, the elf Hydrating Face Primer is a lightweight and hydrating option that provides a natural matte finish. While it didn't completely meet my personal expectations in terms of pore-filling and line-smoothing abilities, it has proven to be a great fit for my niece's dry skin. If you have similar skin concerns, this primer may be worth a try.

title: Bew√§hrte Revolution Qualit√§t
review: Darf beim MakeUp nicht fehlen, wenn man das Baking bevorzugt. Habe bisher als MakeUp Artist nie ein anderes Powder gehabt. Ich m√∂chte es auch gar nicht ausprobieren.Es passt sich farblich gut an.Ich nutze es unter den Augen, ein wenig am Nasenr√ºcken, ein wenig am Kinn, einen Klecks auf der Stirn und jeweils einen schmalen Streifen an den Wangen unterhalb der dunklen Kontur. So kommt die Kontur besser zur Geltung.Eine gute Grundlage ist ein Muss. Die Foundation bzw der Concealer sollte daf√ºr geeignet sein. Wer dazu neigt, dass sich das MakeUp in den F√§ltchen absetzt, sollte an den Stellen auf das Powder verzichten.Immer auf die Menge achten.Ich mache mir ein wenig von dem Produkt in ein Sch√§lchen und nehme es direkt mit dem Blending Sponge auf und tupfe es damit vorsichtig auf. Das lasse ich dort so, bis ich den Rest vom MakeUp (Lidschatten etc) fertig habe und verblende dann (ohne Druck) alles mit einem gro√üen fluffigen Pinsel. Das l√§sst das Powder ebenm√§√üig erscheinen und entfernt √ºbersch√ºssiges Powder.Wer Probleme mit diesem Produkt hat, sollte sich erst ein "wie mach ich das" - Video anschauen, bevor man dem Produkt die Schuld gibt, denn beim Baking kann man viel falsch machen ebenso bei den Pinseln und Schw√§mmen.Wer zu viel Powder benutzt oder es mit zu viel Druck auftr√§gt oder verteilt, der wird nachher sehen, dass das Produkt unsch√∂ne R√§nder hinterl√§sst und buchst√§blich br√∂ckelt.Ich hoffe, ich konnte helfen.

title: Love the formula and great intro to cream contour
review: Just looking for an affordable introduction to practice my cream contour. Nyx surprised me with it formula which is easy to apply, easy to work with, and lasts all day. I compare it to other products I've tried such as Colourpop and ABH creams, and Maybelline and Wet 'n Wild liquids.I gave it four stars because I think I can safely assume you will only use 2-3 colors. It's great for finding a match for your medium shade, but there's only going to be one darker shade and one (maybe two) light shade. I wouldn't necessarily buy this again now that I know what colors I actually use and would then look for a larger 3-pan kit from Nyx.Also of note: I use the technique where you apply the contour before foundation. I mention this because I apply the contour a little heavier and lean into the drama. Once you apply foundation, you can blend out and soften it up. I think this technique also helps with the ease of use and product longevity. If you use a different technique, I imagine you might have a different experience with this product (but maybe not!)

title: Gives a natural result
review: This eyebrow palette is very small, you could pop this in your handbag for touch ups quite easily. I bought the Medium Brown as I am quite fair skinned. The left hand colour is the wax, the right hand colour is the setting/filling powder. One of the application brushes is firmer than the other and is for applying the wax. The softer one is for the powder. The brushes are very small, though, so I think I might buy some full size ones as the supplied ones are ok for carry around but are a bit fiddly to use.Application was easy enough, and I'm a total beginner at this! As a 60-something lady I have quite sparse brows now so I was looking for something to add a little colour and definition to what little I have left. The wax part of the procedure went on nicely and helped smooth and define the brow shape. The powder needs a little more care as it can be pretty dark if you use too much. If dark and thick is what you want I'm sure you could achieve that but us older gals need something more subtle and it does that too as I hope you can see from my before/after photo (my first attempt!).Overall my first impression of this little kit is pretty good. I'm actually quite new to doing make-up and I've been searching for something reliable for my eyebrows. I tried a propelling wax pencil that broke off after a dozen uses and wouldn't have lasted long anyway there was so little in it, and also a traditional brow pencil that proved impossible to sharpen reliably. Two expensive and disappointing products. There's very little to go wrong with this type of palette and brush style of brow grooming and the price makes it a good value product. I figure it should last me a few months at least so I'm hopeful this is the answer for me. I can recommend you give it a try if you have experienced similar problems and frustrations with eyebrow products as I have.

title: A great lipstick that lasts and stays without drying out your lips
review: NOTE WELL!  Do as much research as possible on the color you're thinking about getting, as I had the misfortune of purchasing an everyday shade ("Lead the Way") that was wayyyy too pale for my complexion. As it wasn't returnable, I basically gave it to my fairer-skinned mom as a gift. Watch Tiktoks and Youtube reviews with people close to your coloring to get a real idea of what it will look like on you, as the pictures can and even tend to be inaccurate. And make sure you know whether it's returnable before you buy that color.As for the product itself, it's really exceptional for such a good price. Feels great on your lips, lasts a crazy long time, unlikely to get on your teeth -- just a really great lipstick. I, falling toward a more olive complexion with yellow undertones,  found the best to be:-"Own Your Empire" is an absolutely perfect red. Think Peggy Carter from Captain America. I'm in love with it, just on the SLIGHTEST blue side of the orange/blue red lipstick scale. Anyone who's had issues with their One Red Lipstick being a little too orange, this one's for you.-"Pave the Road" is an excellent, subtle shade that's just slightly darker and richer than my natural lip color -- really great for everyday.-"Chase Dreams" is a more fun, slightly lavender-tilted option for when you're wearing clothes that don't look great with straight-up red.I'm one of those people who frowns at paying $8 for one lipstick, but it's really worth it.  Good luck!

title: This thing works AMAZING‚Ä¶.on some people
review: Yes; it‚Äôs like clear pasty glue. And that‚Äôs why it worked for me. I‚Äôm a pro athlete and I sweat gallons. I don‚Äôt wear a lot of makeup but I have adult acne blemishes and dark spots that no one ever sees thanks to a combination of products; STARTING with this primer. I don‚Äôt use a lot and I rub it in my skin immediately as once it dries, that‚Äôs it! It stays put, and so will whatever you apply on top of it. So careful. A little goes a long way and you must spread it well and thin. It feels thick but once rubbed in your fingers it kind of gets more malleable. I only put in my t zone and cheeks; avoiding eye area completely. Otherwise it will pull your skin and make you look wrinkly.I dab a little MAC concealer over the blemishes and spots, spray a brush with Airbrush foundation (Jerome Alexander or Dior) and a bit of powder (MAC FIT or inexpensive Coty Mineral Translucent) and BOOM. Perfect looking face!! Even my dermatologist compliments me on how my face looks and how I cover up my uneven color and blemishes.I don‚Äôt put a picture here of before and after (I should) but Im not going to embarrass myself with my before look. It works for some people like me. I hope this works for you because for me this was a life changer. From sweaty makeup mess and nosy people asking about my blemishes and dark spots (rude). Now no one has to obsess over my post 40 acne blemishes and we all can move on to truly important things.FYI‚Äôs: No scent. A tube lasts me about two months of daily use. Not sold anymore in my local pharmacy. Hard to find; not sure why. I have combination skin that is dry on the forehead. Acne prone. No issues with clogged pores or pimples.

title: SUPER MATTE - Not for the faint of heart!
review: Alright so I just received this and am gonna list my thoughts on a first impression basis:It has the look and consistency of very thick petroleum jelly, to the point where it takes a bit of muscle to squeeze out of the tube. I got a bit skeptical, because I've used clear primers in the past (the Smashbox one and Maybelline Master Prime) that haven't lived up to their claims of blurring pores and making your makeup last. I also was thinking it may be difficult to spread evenly over the skin, since it's sooo thiccccc! But, just like with petroleum jelly, once it hits the warmth of your skin, it just melts into a much more malleable consistency.This is when the stuff starts to behave VERY differently from your everyday vaseline...Instead of sitting on top of your skin in a layer of grease, it fully absorbs into your pores, and ANY trace of oil or moisture is GONE! So are your pores! The skin on my face literally feels TIGHT!That being said, WHOO! BE CAREFUL!I have hyperhidrosis (AKA excessive sweating, especially from my head and face, which is like the suckiest thing ever) - and the reason I mention it is because I have tried antiperspirant face lotions that feel A LOT like this. I couldn't find a list of ingredients on the package, but if I had to guess, I would say that this stuff contains aluminum (maybe even a lot of it) which will clog your pores and form a barrier between your skin and the oxygen. In other words, if you are super oily and acne-prone like I used to be, this will help control it for a special occasion here and there, but will make your skin 1,000% worse in the long run if you use it on a regular basis! - Again, that's only my first impression, but if your skin does not take kindly to strange new cosmetic formulas, I would use this stuff very sparingly.My skin does get noticeably more oily in the summer, and I usually LOVE a matte primer, but this is the first time I felt like a product made my skin look dried out and wrinkled. I bought it thinking it would help my makeup wear longer, I had no expectations that it would be so matte and blurring. I'm shook if you can't tell, lolOverall - I REALLY really like this primer, and if I had to bet I would say it's going to keep my makeup in place 1000% longer than any other I've tried, but it's also a weapon you must use with caution! lol

It's a very beautiful look for those who want a dewy look.  For reference, I have very fair skin.  My only complaint is that it is thick and the dropper is not the best delivery method.  It should be in a tube, and L‚ÄôOr√©al needs to address this and redo the packaging.  I took one star off for this reason. title: Great lip liner for the price
review: So- this lip liner is the matte dryer waxy kind (not the type that glides and feels moisturizing). However, I personally prefer this type as I find they last longer and look the most realistic if you like to subtly overline. The shade peekaboo neutral is for you if you have naturally light/medium true pink lips (or want it to match a lipstick in that range)- it will be the PERFECT slight overline shade. Does not have a cool/grey undertone. If you prefer that try the shade natural. It's a bit deeper and slightly more neutral rather than pink. Nude pink is significantly lighter/brighter pink than both peekaboo and natural. It would be best for lips that are naturally quite a light/brighter pink. I adore this lip liner for the price especially.

I layer my setting powder on top which helps keep oil from building up throughout my shift. I don't use more expensive ones to compare this to, but if you're looking for something lower cost this is a great option. One bottle lasts me about 4 months and I use anywhere from 5-7 sprays across my face almost daily. I also have sensitive skin and easily break out, and this has never given me any issues.

title: Doesn't fully clean, but It's not the worst
review: Cleaning makeup brushes is personally annoying from water everywhere, hands getting pruney, etc, it's not fun. I had a Lumia 2 Makeup Brush Cleaner, and you're better off doing it yourself. I've tried the scrubbing mat, and honestly, those so far are the best way to properly wash them. So when I came across this, I was ridiculously excited to try it. Here are my thoughts:Pro:- It's the quickest way to clean your brushes- leaves little to no mess (assuming the water is below the max line)- dries extremely quickly (preventing growing bacteria, in theory)- Battery operated (But, sadly it dies quickly)Cons:- it doesn't wash your brushes 100% ( If you are lazy, I would recommend doing this daily and once a week manually hand washing it.. or at least monthly)- The attachment doesn't fit all brushes (some are too tight or way too loose)- Some attachments might fit quiet snugly that the handle and bristle might get broken, which isn't fun when using expensive brushes- I personally don't agree with drying your brush without rinsing it out first

title: A great device but...
review: the company really needs to update the description of this product.  It does not come with 13 different sized brush handle collars, there is no USB connectivity, and there is no cleaning pad.  So wish all this was included!  It comes with 8 collars and is battery (2 AAA, not included) operated.  With this said, I will say it's a great device.  I cleaned 5 brushes in the span of approximately 10 minutes or so and could probably have done that in less time if I hadn't been so fascinated by this little machine.  Just a note - take care when removing the collar from each brush.  If the brush handle is stuck in the collar, I think it's best to remove the collar & brush from the unit and then remove the brush from the collar.  This will help avoid breaking the spindle on the cleaner handle (although they do provide 2 spindles) and the spindle, once inserted in the main handle, is not removed.  Personally, I really don't enjoy cleaning my makeup brushes.  It's tough to get them any where like when they were new and the drying time seems like forever.  This cleaner is a game changer.

title: Nice budget friendly set with plenty of brushes!
review: I ordered the 25 piece makeup brushes set in the color option "Brown" the set is accurate to what I expected to receive.These are decent quality makeup brushes, a great price point for 25 brushes.  The set is great for beginners, teens and adults alike.The brushes are soft and nicely done, even.  They pick up makeup well and work well to distribute product, on my skin.The brush lengths are great, comfortable to use, and light weight.I particularly like that this set came with so many brushes, it makes for a great set to gift for anyone.Decent quality and and over all good product.

title: Decent budget friendly set
review: This is a pretty good set for the price. Would be great for someone starting out, or if you needed more brushes but didn't want to spend a fortune. You get a lot of brushes in this set, and the bristles are soft and pretty dense. I find these wash well and don't shed too much. I don't find every brush to be useful, as some just don't serve any purpose for me, but that's just personal preference. I think these pick up product fairly well, some work better than others. The handles and bristle portion are glued on well, which is great to see. No chemical or dye smells to these. Overall it's a pretty decent set for the price.

title: A Complete Set of Make Up Brushes
review: The MAANGE 25Pcs Makeup Brushes is a complete set that looks good attractive on my bathroom counter.Each brush is shaped differently to cover very face and eye application.The brushes are lightweight and comfortable to hold.The bristles are soft, easy to apply, gentle on the skin, do not shed and clean well.The handles are made of wood and appear to be durable.The brushes come individually packaged and are labeled for easy identification.The brushes have an odd, strong smell that lingers even after washing them.Overall, a great set for beginners or make up enthusiasts.

title: Full set of25 brushes with WHAT they are for Written on them
review:
The media could not be loaded.
                
            
                
            
            
        
    
    
Ok so there are25 different brushes you get in this makeup set.For me  the best part is that each brush is labeled for what its used for. This is so helpful!!! Like what type of brush it is for which face part or makeup application job.So for example one brush may say for contour or another for eyes / eyebrows etc.Each brush head shape and size varies accoding to its purpose. The bristles are synthetic and nylon to be more specific. They are soft and infact would have prefered some to not be as soft especially for contouring.I personally am not gonna use all these brushes because my makeup routine is not so complex but for sure there are a few that will be very useful.The brushes are attractive , lightweight and easy to clean because I found they dried very fast.I hope this helps

title: Lots of brushes
review: I would like to apologize to every woman that wears makeup.  I had no idea that there were so many different types of brushes to apply different makeup and such for every part of your face.  Twenty five to be exact.  No wonder it takes them so long to get ready.  Pure madness.  I got this for my wife to shorten her getting ready and apply makeup time, but all it did was make that time longer.  Each brush has a specific use and is for a specific part of the face.  An artist doesn't have these many brushes.  It's a good thing though so you don't mix colours and cross contaminate the brushes.  These brushes need to be washed before using them because they have a bad odour to them and you don't want to take chances that your face will break out or have an adverse affect.  Now all you need is a nice container to hold them all and have them at your finger tips.  I particularly like that each brush is labelled to tell you what it is used for.

title: A great lipstick that lasts and stays without drying out your lips
review: NOTE WELL!  Do as much research as possible on the color you're thinking about getting, as I had the misfortune of purchasing an everyday shade ("Lead the Way") that was wayyyy too pale for my complexion. As it wasn't returnable, I basically gave it to my fairer-skinned mom as a gift. Watch Tiktoks and Youtube reviews with people close to your coloring to get a real idea of what it will look like on you, as the pictures can and even tend to be inaccurate. And make sure you know whether it's returnable before you buy that color.As for the product itself, it's really exceptional for such a good price. Feels great on your lips, lasts a crazy long time, unlikely to get on your teeth -- just a really great lipstick. I, falling toward a more olive complexion with yellow undertones,  found the best to be:-"Own Your Empire" is an absolutely perfect red. Think Peggy Carter from Captain America. I'm in love with it, just on the SLIGHTEST blue side of the orange/blue red lipstick scale. Anyone who's had issues with their One Red Lipstick being a little too orange, this one's for you.-"Pave the Road" is an excellent, subtle shade that's just slightly darker and richer than my natural lip color -- really great for everyday.-"Chase Dreams" is a more fun, slightly lavender-tilted option for when you're wearing clothes that don't look great with straight-up red.I'm one of those people who frowns at paying $8 for one lipstick, but it's really worth it.  Good luck!

title: Love these!
review: I have had these brushes for a little over a year at this point and absolutely love them.I really can't find anything negative to say about them.I suppose if I were to try hard, my only complaints would be a) they do take a couple days to dry after washing & b) I would prefer for one of the fluffy angled brushes -simply because there are two that are nearly identical- to be replaced with a larger fluffy dome brush (BS-Mall sells one in another set of theirs that is fantastic). However, that is just me being a little fussy. The drying time doesn't bother me really. More so a heads up for anyone who is use to their brushes drying more quickly.All of these brushes perform just as they should & better than you would expect considering the price. They all pick up & deposit color very very well. I find that they perform as well with liquid/cream products as they do with powders. The top of bristles are white which allows you to see how much product you have picked up & what you may have used them with last. This also helps you see/decide when you may need to clean them. They are fluffy & soft but nicely dense.The large tapered/pointed face brush is more stiff than the other face brushes but still as soft. This makes it nice for applying setting powder under the eyes or areas that need concentrated placement.I appreciate the shorter handles on the face brushes. I find them much easier to use than longer handled brushes I've owned/tried in the past. They are just the right length. Not so short that you feel you lose control or may drop them but not so long that you feel as though you are flopping them around when you are applying makeup.I still have not seen Any bristles come out of Any of these brushes! This surprises me. I also have washed them many times and they are still holding strong. None of the ferrules have come off of the handles & none of the brush heads are misshapen as of yet. I do always dry them upside down after washing.Overall, these are fantastic brushes & you absolutely cannot beat the price. I have had very nice brushes in the past...that were much much much more expensive.... yet, I do not see myself going back to them. They are really on an, at least, equal level...I even prefer these over many of those! Just saying...You may need to fill in this set with a few pieces (large fluffy powder brush, eyebrow spoolie, lash/brow comb, etc) but there aren't many you'd need & you could easily apply all of your makeup with just this set if you needed/wanted.I can't imagine ever regretting a purchase from this company. To date, I've bought at least 3 different sets from this seller & have been equally pleased with them all.Just buy them! You can't beat the price to quality & their money back guarantee is peace of mind anyway.*I paid for these with my OWN money at the full price they were listed. I did NOT receive these for free or at a discount. I was NOT asked to alter or "up" rate my review. Even if I were ever approached to do so, I would always rate & review items at my own honest opinion. I'm a stay at home Mom of four (& homeschool), so I can be pretty picky about what I've spent our money on :P I hate the dishonest/"bought" reviews. I always appreciate the ones who have been provided the product for free or at a discount, yet are still honest, twice as much. Rant over ;) *
date: Reviewed in the United States on 28 December 2017

title: Great brushes foe the price
review: These brushes are great! They are soft yet sturdy! The variety of all the brushes for the price, you really can't beat! If the outside container really bothers you, you could always gift them in a cute brush bag but honestly the container is def great for traveling and if you wanted to just use it as cups to hold the brushes both the top & bottom of the container are large enough to hold brushes so you can separate the set out according to how you like and the brushes will not fall over. I was actually surprised how nice they are. On the brushes themselves, it has the name/what the brush is for so if you lose the little information pack that comes in the package, don't worry! They have everything from foundation brushes to extremely thin liquid eyeliner brushes that honestly could be used for nail art if you're into that (that's now thin and precise it is).  I would def recommend this, esp for a gift. It looks high end and feels high end.

title: not as versatile as one would think
review: they are not that soft, I have seen better ones in the drug store, but for value they will suffice.  I have used a couple of the brushes only thus far.  Specifically for the  exact reason I purchased them.  I Am experimenting with Cheekbone Beauty products but I  find that just using my fingers is not sufficient.  So I have used 2 of the larger brushes to  blend that product out  (using a color for undereye concealer)  and it works okay but it definitely  is not as soft as I was expecting for that delicate area.  None of them are.  The smaller brushes  are too small for that purpose.  I just fell that although the price point is great they are not the best BUDGET  brushes out there.I was never a big fan of makeup, when I was younger and did makeup  daily it consisted of  eyeshadow, liner, mascara, a bit of blush  and a lip gloss.  Now that I am older I rarely  wear any makeup, my eyelashes seem to be shorter and I have dark circles under my eyes.  So my main  purpose today is if I am going out to look less tired, I use some concealer,  do my  very sparse eyebrows and  a touch of  mascara. Maybe a little blush and of course a lip balm  Most of the brushes I got in this set for me go unused unless I decide to  do what I once did, but  I do not feel the need to.  I did go to the drug store and get another brush  that is much softer  and there is a world of difference in how soft it is compared to these.  But it is a different brush, a size that is not included in this set.  I have also used one of the brushes for the  cheekbone beauty primer stick,  to  stipple it on as that makes it easier to use the  Unify fair1 as a concealer on that very delicate under eye area.  I personally would not recommend purchasing this set  and I will eventually  get the brushes I  want that yes do cost more, but are softer and less likely to pull and tug on your skin.  Once I  play with more eye makeup like shadows I may  see how well the smaller brushes do for that, but for now for what I need these were not the best choice.

title: I had no idea what I was missing!
review: Background: Thought I'd write this up, because as a person who prefers sheer but effective foundation & concealer coverage AND spends a lot of time in front of cameras for my job as an online instructor to a global audience in HD, finding stuff that makes my skin feel fresh & flawless at 50 is important to me, not only for the cameras, but for myself too.I bought this concealer brush as a bit of an impulse buy during Prime Day (along with a new foundation brush) because I'd seen various makeup videos on YouTube using similar ones. I have always used my fingers, and had no idea that a brush would give such superior results.I have very naturally youthful, wrinkle-free skin for my age, but my skin is getting more delicate and thinner. My night owl tendencies are more obvious under my eyes as well...Being able to more precisely & delicately apply & manipulate concealer is a godsend!And when concealer is settling into the under eye skin, you can easily use this brush (after wiping off any excess product on the bristles) to sweep away any concealer that has collected in the fine crease under the lash line.I've tried it with three different liquid concealers of various price points: NYX HD, Too Faced, and Make Up For Ever HD. All went on beautifully, and I'd rate them in that order too (Make Up For Ever being the most impressive finish).I am hooked.I only recently switched to using a foundation brush (a cheap one, but it has converted me), so I can't wait until the Real Techniques one I also bought on Prime Day arrives.When cash allows, I'll upgrade from both of these by Real Techniques to pro-level brushes, but for now? For now, I look better than ever before, and am thrilled.
date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 14 July 2022

title: I might have messed mine up???
review: This is my first time using a product like this. I have NEVER washed my brushes. That‚Äôs a lie‚Ä¶I washed a couple of them about 5 years ago with just soap and water, and they stayed damp forever, and I then I couldn‚Äôt use them for days. But I‚Äôve been seeing these kits on Buzzfeed for years now, and since i‚Äôm approaching 40, I'm trying to take better care of myself. I didn‚Äôt look at the instructions before my first attempt. It comes with these 2 little white pegs. I put it on incorrectly the first time, and I had to use a kitchen tool to remove it, with quite a bit of force. Then I see the instructions and it says that once it‚Äôs in there, don‚Äôt remove it. So I have no idea why they sent 2 of it‚Äôs not meant to be replaced. Anyway, I got the hang of it, but I don‚Äôt know if I messed something up with the yanking or if it‚Äôs just the weight of the brushes. When I turn it on, I have to start the spinning off with my hand. Again, that might be my fault. It is very cool to watch though. I like how quickly they dry with the spinning. If they made stuff like this when I was in my youth, then yes, I would‚Äôve washed my brushes regularly. Like I seriously have one powder brush that I‚Äôve had for over 10 years and this was the first time it was cleaned. Be careful with the big brushes though, and how you store them after cleaning. The wand on that one broke off years ago, but it‚Äôs so big that I didn‚Äôt need it. I have a mug that I set all of my brushes in, and bc I don‚Äôt have the stem on that brush it went into the mug, and got beaten up by other brush stems. When I finally went to use that one again, the fibers were going every which way. I don‚Äôt know if I ruined the brush. I‚Äôll try to wash it again and hopefully the shape comes back‚Ä¶but if it doesn‚Äôt, we‚Äôll, I‚Äôve been needed to retire that thing for years now!!
date: Reviewed in the United States on 22 February 2022

title: Great product! However it has some downsides

But that takes a lot of time, and sometimes with denser brushes soapy residue is really hard to get out which annoys me to no end. Let me start by saying, it works! It doesn‚Äôt get all the staining out if you use bright colors like I like to do, but it gets all the pigment out. If you have double sided brushes, this could be a problem if you want to clean both sides, because chances are that you will only be able to clean the larger side of the brush, because the attachment won‚Äôt fit if you turn it around to clean the other side, it‚Äôll just screw up your brush and fly off. But it came with enough attachments to fit all of my brushes! Another thing, make sure you have multiple triple A batteries in rotation before you start using this. This thing eats through them like no ones business, so buy the value pack if you have a lot of brushes like I do. But it‚Äôs a small price to pay for your sanity as I‚Äôd rather buy more batteries then go back to scrubbing my brushes constantly. All and all it‚Äôs a good product, and would recommend buying it if you‚Äôre like me and have to wash a lot of brushes constantly.

title: Works, but not like magic!
review: It‚Äôs been a long time since I‚Äôve cleaned my brushes, let‚Äôs just say that. My foundation brush is newer, but it was still pretty filthy as the bristles are very compact. It took a few sessions to really get that, my powder, & blush/highlighter brushes very clean. What I suggest you do is:- fill an empty water bottle with lukewarm water & soap/brush cleaner, you‚Äôll use that to refill your cleansing bowl.- have a secondary container to place the used water in.Follow the directions provided in the packaging, but without drying your brushes completely. Check your bristles to see if you need to continue cleaning. I typically only had to do this on the large face brushes. If the water is starting to get very dirty, I discard it in the second bowl & refill the the water bottle. Once clean, dry all the way.The smaller brushes dry VERY QUICKLY for the most part, so be careful not to over dry them. I suggest drying them slowly & reshaping the bristles as you go. It‚Äôs very easy to overspin & ended up with your bristles bushy.

I use it mostly at home, but there have been days in which I‚Äôve had to rush out of the house without my makeup, so I grab my makeup bag and the mirror and I‚Äôll put my makeup on in a parking lot later that day! Just place the suction cup from the extension, onto your windshield and voila, you‚Äôre good to go! Sometimes the suction needs a little moisture, I mean that‚Äôs something I thought everyone knew but apparently some people are writing in their reviews that the suction doesn‚Äôt work. üôÉ I‚Äôm pretty sure they‚Äôre not putting a little moisture (from the faucet if you‚Äôre in the bathroom, but a little lick will do in a pinch, don‚Äôt say ‚Äògross,‚Äô you‚Äôve all done it ) on the suction cup will make it work just fine, unless the suction cup happens to be defective, which I doubt.The mirror works great! It does need batteries, so I bought the Amazon rechargeable batteries and charger, specifically for this mirror because it might end up using 3 AA batteries about once a month, depending on how long it takes to do your makeup. My kids also use the mirror for some reason (despite the fact that they have perfect vision) so our batteries wear out fairly quickly, as well as the fact that I use the mirror daily and for at least 1/2 an hour a day. Amazon rechargeable batteries don‚Äôt keep the brightness as long, but as long as you don‚Äôt mind charging them regularly, that‚Äôs fine, otherwise regular batteries keep the brightness for a lot longer.  It‚Äôs sturdy too! I‚Äôve dropped it many times, due to clumsiness, and it keeps on ticking.Lastly, as I recall, the company is woman owned, so that‚Äôs another plus! If you‚Äôre about to turn 40, or you know a contact lense wearer or makeup wearer, or even a skin care enthusiast, get it for yourself or a friend! It‚Äôs definitely worth it! ü§©I should add that I just remembered that when I originally ordered the mirror, it didn‚Äôt come with the extension and it was during Covid, so not only did I have to wait for it for almost a month, but had to pay extra for something I assumed came with it, since the photo included the extension. So there‚Äôs that. But it was worth it! Honestly, I think they should just include the extension (and charge more) because I don‚Äôt see how anyone could use it without it. It doesn‚Äôt really stand up on its own, I don‚Äôt believe.

title: Great Zoeva Dupes. Natural Hair Brushes Have a Learning Curve.
review: 1. White hair brushes typically indicate animal (natural) hair. These are meant for dense application of powder products. The black hair brushes are synthetic, for cream and liquid products (they don't soak up the product as much as natural hair does) and lighter powder application (they don't grab powder as well as natural hair). That's why the eyeshadow brushes and blush, highlight, etc brushes in this set are natural hair and the foundation, duo fiber, brow and powder are synthetic (you want a light dusting of powder for all over). It's hard to find natural hair brushes in this price range and these are really good! They are a natural-synthetic blend. That's also why some people are saying the white hair brushes shed and fray more than the synthetic (black) ones-- that's not uncommon and they may not be washing them properly. Please research how to wash your natural hair brushes! Condition them or use oil to keep them from fraying; treat them like your own hair. Natural hair brushes will change your makeup game!2. These brushes are meant to be Zoeva dupes, down to the name and number on the handle and the natural-synthetic composition. I own some of the Z ones these are meant to dupe and Jessup are really good quality for the price! The Z ones are a little softer, but even those can shed a bit at first. I've included a comparison photo. I haven't washed the Jessup brushes yet, so I'll update once I do about how they hold their shape.3. Most of the brushes are pretty self explanatory, but some of them might seem superfluous. Some suggestions for the ones that seem extra: 110 Face Shape for cream contour, 122 Petit Stippling for targeted bronzer, 101 Luxe Face Definer for diffused bronzer, 109 Luxe Face Paint for powder contour and 125 Stippling for light liquid foundation or tinted moisturizer.Overall, this is a LOVELY comprehensive brush set! I've had them about a month. The eye brushes are especially impressive. You can do any look with this range! The synthetic face brushes rival Zoeva quality, except the Z ones are heavier without sparkles on handle but who cares. The white hair brushes are also very good. All brushes are dense, so soft, great blending, don't leave streaks, solid construction. These Jessup brushes are a STEAL. You can find cheaper brush sets on Amazon, but they will be synthetic bristles. These are some very good quality brushes. 10/10 recommend.

title: The ONLY Review You Need to Read! GET IT!!
review: If you‚Äôre a cheapo that likes high quality things such as myself, THESE BRUSHES ARE PERFECT. They are VERY comparable to Morphe Brushes, and dare I say, these Jessup brushes are even BETTER. They‚Äôre soft without feeling plastic-y (only one really had a ‚Äúsynthetic‚Äù feel to it, which is the 125 Stippling brush) and they apply makeup better than a lot of higher-end brushes that I‚Äôve tried in the past. I got the color in Blushing Bride and they are absolutely beautiful! All of the brushes come individually packaged in a plastic wrapper; the bigger, fluffier brushes have a net-like thing on the bristles which protects them (only 24 brushes are shown in the picture because one brush had rolled under my leg, so none were missing). I‚Äôve seen reviews complaining about a hair or two being out of place, but personally, I see no issue in that; none of my brushes were shedding or fuzzy-looking.I‚Äôm not a picky person, but if YOUR brushes don‚Äôt come in in tip-top shape, send them back and get a new batch because these are worth it despite any minor flaw!!I only used 7 of the 25 brushes to apply my makeup for the look I created in these pictures for my everyday routine. I used all of my same products; however, I did not apply or blend my foundation with any of the brushes *out of preference*, so I CAN‚ÄôT say how these brushes would handle blending liquid foundation.Brushes Used:I used the 105 Luxe Highlight brush to apply my setting/baking powder (as shown in the second picture), and it picked up my Fenty Beauty setting powder really well and applied just how I wanted it to.110 Face Shape brush: Essence powder contour around face and nose- this brush is super small to be contouring or bronzing the cheeks, but none of the others seemed to be the right shape or density besides the brush I had already used to apply my blush.127 Luxe Sheer Cheek brush: NARS powder blush- this one didn‚Äôt apply my blush exactly how I liked, so I would simply use a different brush next time. This one would‚Äôve been the better cheek contour brush for its shape.322 Brow Liner: brows using ABH dip brow pomade- was a bit big for applying this product, so next time I would swap it out for the 312 Detail Liner brush (disclaimer: none of these eye brushes have a ‚Äúspoolie‚Äù to brush and blend out brow products)228 Luxe Crease, 227 Luxe Soft Definer, and 226 Smudger brushes: eyeshadow with my GlamLite Chocolate Donut Palette and The Chocolates Palette by Juvia‚Äôs Place- these eyeshadow brushes really knocked everything out of the park even though I only used 3 of the 15 EYE brushes in this 25pc set.Keep in mind to not rely solely on pictures of how makeup applied for others in reviews because makeup primer, brand, and skills OR lack of those things can affect how these brushes will APPEAR to perform.All of the brushes are different so DON‚ÄôT expect multiples; if you do lots of colorful eyeshadow looks very often, I would purchase this set along with Jessup‚Äôs brush set that comes with JUST the 15 or 18 eye brushes which is $25.99 if I‚Äôm remembering correctly.I cannot say for certain how these brushes would hold up during a wash because I try not to wash my makeup brushes as often as I should, but these are SO nice that I wouldn‚Äôt even mind if they got a little bit beat up because I would keep using them and continue buying more. These would be an amazing gift to anyone that has a love for makeup or even anyone that is a beginner in the makeup world.
